The Benue State Government has sacked the Vice-Chairman, Lobi Stars, Football Club (FC), Makurdi, Tama Aondofa over his poor outing since he assumed leadership of the team. Chairman, Lobi Stars FC, Engr Benson Abounu who announced Aondofaâ€™s sack on Monday, said he extracted a resignation letter from the former Vice-Chairman the same day. He also announced the immediate appointment of Ex-Super Eagles international, Dominic Iorfa as the new Vice-Chairman and handler of Lobi Stars FC. Abounu who is also the state deputy governor noted that the change became inevitable in order to meet the yearnings and aspirations of fans and the people of the state. Responding, Dominic Iorfa pledged he would do his best to rescue the team, which is relegation bound. He gave the state government the assurance that he would work assiduously to keep the team above waters. Captain of Lobi Stars, Solomon Kwambe appreciated the state government for listening to the voice of reason, adding that the team would play its heart out so that it escapes relegation.